<li id="cite_note-121"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-121">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFGamliel1984" class="citation journal cs1">Gamliel, Amram (1 January 1984). "A Spark of Enlightenment Among the Jews of Yemen". <i>Hebrew Studies</i>. <b>25</b>: 82–89. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/27908885">27908885</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Hebrew+Studies&amp;rft.atitle=A+Spark+of+Enlightenment+Among+the+Jews+of+Yemen&amp;rft.volume=25&amp;rft.pages=82-89&amp;rft.date=1984-01-01&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F27908885%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft.aulast=Gamliel&amp;rft.aufirst=Amram&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AKabbalah" class="Z3988"></span></span>
