<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Originally a <a href="/wiki/Mishnaic_Hebrew" title="Mishnaic Hebrew">Mishnaic Hebrew</a> term for <a href="/wiki/Nach_(Bible_acronym)" class="mw-redirect" title="Nach (Bible acronym)">Nakh</a>, the term was commonly used to mean 'received tradition' or 'chain of tradition' by the <a href="/wiki/Geonic" class="mw-redirect" title="Geonic">Geonic</a> period.</span>
